narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I have enjoyed this section of our course- I have learned a great deal about cell biology and disease mechanisms that fits well with our other medical coursework.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think the lectures by Dr. Takizawa are very clear and well done. I wish it would made a bit more clear to us how our grades will be determined in the end.

The organization is good. Due to the integrative nature of the medical curriculum, sometimes it's hard to determine whether material is "strictly cell biology" or not -- this doesn't matter so much in the day-to-day, but will factor in the calculation of the final grade for the class, so it may help to have a better idea of where these questions may come from. Not necessarily because this information is more important than the rest (or less), but because if MD-PhD students are graded on the cell bio portion differently from they are graded on the other portions of the class, it would help to be aware of which material will be emphasized for the cell bio portion so that we can prepare to study for that differently, if we must!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I think this is a great way to learn medically-relevant biological mechanisms.
